5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROHIBITING A RETIRED JUDGE OR JUSTICE FROM SERVING
6 IN ANY CASE IN WHICH A PARTY CHALLENGES THE CONSTITUTIONALITY OF A STATE STATUTE;
7 AMENDING SECTIONS 3-5-202 AND 19-5-103, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11
12 Section 1. Section 3-5-202, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "3-5-202. Qualifications and residence. (1) A person is not eligible for the office of judge of a district
14 court unless the person is a citizen of the United States, has resided in the state 2 years immediately before
15 taking office, and has been admitted to practice law in Montana for at least 5 years prior to the date of
16 appointment or election.
17 (2) A judge of a district court need not be a resident of the district for which the judge is elected or
18 appointed at the time of election or appointment, but after election or appointment, the judge must reside in the
19 district for which the judge is elected or appointed during the judge's term of office.
20 (3) A retired judge or justice is not eligible to serve in any case in which a party challenges the
21 constitutionality of a state statute."
22
23 Section 2. Section 19-5-103, MCA, is amended to read:
24 "19-5-103. Call of retired judges and justices and inactive vested members for duty --
25 exception. (1) (a) If Except as provided in subsection (2), if physically and mentally able, a retired judge or
26 justice who has voluntarily retired after at least 8 years of service is subject to call for duty by the chief justice to
27 aid and assist any district court or any water court under directions that the chief justice may give or to serve as
28 water judge.
