1 (b) When called, a retired judge's or justice's duties include the examination of the facts, cases,
2 and authorities cited and the preparation of opinions for and on behalf of the court to which the judge or justice
3 is called to serve. The opinions, when and if and to the extent approved by the court, may be ordered by the
4 court to constitute the opinion of the court. The court and the retired judge or justice may, subject to any rule
5 that the supreme court may adopt, perform any duties that are not inconsistent with the constitution of the state.
6 (2) A retired judge or justice may not aid and assist in any case in which a party challenges the
7 constitutionality of a state statute.
8 (3) (a) A retired judge or justice, when called to duty, must be reimbursed for actual expenses, if
9 any, in responding to the call.
10 (b) In addition, a retired judge or justice is entitled to receive compensation in an amount equal to:
11 (i) the daily salary then currently applicable to the judicial position in which the duty is rendered for
12 each day of duty rendered, up to a total of 180 days in a calendar year; and
13 (ii) for each day of duty after 180 days in a calendar year, one-twentieth of the monthly salary then
14 currently applicable to the judicial position in which the duty is rendered minus an amount equal to one-
15 twentieth of the monthly retirement benefit that the retired judge or justice is receiving, if any.
16 (4) A judge or justice who is an inactive vested member, who has voluntarily discontinued service
17 as an active judge after at least 8 years of service, and who, by reason of age, is not eligible to receive a
18 retirement benefit under this chapter may be called for duty as provided in subsection (1). A judge or justice
19 called to duty under this subsection must be reimbursed as provided in subsection (2)(a) (3)(a) and
20 compensated as provided in subsection (2)(b)(i) (3)(b)(i) regardless of the number of days served in a calendar
21 year."
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
